&lt;p&gt;
	So, everyone knows John Hancock by the large signature on the Declaration of Independence but what did he do?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Accolades and Accomplishments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Longest serving President of the Second Continental Congress, at 889 days.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		First and Third Governor of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Was the first person to sign the Declaration of Independence&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Worth $350,000 at the time of his death (approximately 1/714th of US GNP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
